
[1]expand

   EXPAND', v.t. [L. expando; es and pando, to open or spread; Eng. span.
   The primary sense is to strain or stretch, and this seems to be the
   sense of bend, L. pandus.]

   1. To open; to spread; as, a flower expands its leaves.

   2. To spread; to enlarge a surface; to diffuse; as, a stream expands
   its waters over a plain.

   3. To dilate; to enlarge in bulk; to distend; as, to expand the chest
   by inspiration; heat expands all bodies; air is expanded by
   rarefaction.

   4. To enlarge; to extend; as, to expand the sphere of benevolence; to
   expand the heart or affections.
